UniCredit Sees Pre-Crisis Risk Costs in Three Years, HN Reports

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-04-18T06:33:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/unicredit-sees-pre-crisis-risk-costs-in-three-years-hn-reports.html
UniCredit SpA (UCG)  expects its costs of
risk to decline to levels last seen before the global financial
crisis in two or three years, Chief Executive Officer  Federico Ghizzoni  said in an interview published in  Hospodarske Noviny .  Italy’s largest bank is considering acquisitions in  Russia ,
 Turkey ,  Poland  and the  Czech Republic  as part of UniCredit’s
expansion plans in central and eastern  Europe , Ghizzoni told the
Prague-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  